      "id": "PopularPost261761",
      "post_content": "I do miss the old art sometimes, especially the stuff Richard Thomas did. I think Wizards went a little too far in hom-ogenizing the art style for newer sets. When I was exposed to the game as a kid, the sheer variety in the artwork was one of the many things I found so cool about Magic. So yeah, keep Wayne Reynolds and Raymond Swanland on board, but bring back Richard Thomas and the Foglios too!",
